The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, June 17 (PTI): Bombay High Court today upheld the decision of the Municipal Corporation of Greater Mumbai to build a security wall around the Siddhivinayak temple in central Mumbai.          
	The order came on a PIL by residents of the area objecting to the construction of the wall, saying it would inconvenience them.                  
	 Sonepat (PTI): A group of women have alleged that they were harassed by policemen in a passenger train, officials said. The men allegedly barged into the reserved coach on Tuesday night, molested them and then fled when the women stopped the train by pulling the emergency chain.                  
	 Houston (PTI): An Indian-American has been appointed deputy mayor of Stafford city in Texas. Ken Mathew is the first person from the community to hold such a post in the US. Originally from Mumbai, Mathew studied at the University of Bombay and the University of Detroit.                  
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): The Kerala cabinet on Wednesday skipped a discussion on governor R.S. Gavais sanction to the CBI to prosecute CPM state secretary Pinarayi Vijayan in a graft case. This was seen as a move to avoid further intra-party differences ahead of the politburo meeting this weekend.                  
	 Meerut (PTI): Curfew was imposed in parts of the city in the small hours of Wednesday after two groups clashed over the parking of a tractor and pelted police with stones. The police used batons to quell the mob. Six persons were injured. Paramilitary forces, including 200 jawans from the RAF, have been deployed.                   
	 London (PTI): A statue of Mahatma Gandhi has been brought to Leicester where it will be unveiled on June 26. Despite opposition by some residents, the city council had cleared the proposal of a charity, Samanwaya Pariwar, to install the statue.                                                                                                                           
